<isis lang="en">
    <stitle>ELECTRICAL SYSTEM TROUBLESHOOTING GUIDE - 9800 - ROCKWELL 9, 10, AND 13 SPEED TRANSMISSIONS - DISASSEMBLE -
        MAINSHAFT
    </stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="disassemble" graphiccount="2">
        <title>MAINSHAFT</title>
        <figure id="f13033f8" figsize="pg-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figg13/G13033f8.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="514px"/>
            <caption>Figure 158. Mainshaft Assembly</caption>
        </figure>
        <para>
            <hotlnk xrefid="f13033f8">Refer to Figure 158.</hotlnk>
        </para>
        <specpara>
            <note>
                <para>The thrust washer on the mainshaft, the snap ring in the reverse gear and the front sliding collar
                    are removed when the mainshaft is removed from the transmission.
                </para>
            </note>
        </specpara>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove the 3rd-4th sliding collar from the mainshaft.</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Put the mainshaft in a vise with brass jaws. Make sure the auxiliary drive gear end of the
                shaft is toward you.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <specpara>
            <note>
                <para>Refer to
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f13033f8">Figure 158</hotlnk>to identify the components of the mainshaft assembly
                    for the transmission models.
                </para>
            </note>
        </specpara>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove the snap ring from the second groove from the top of the shaft.</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Use a small punch to push the key away from roll pin at the bottom of the shaft.</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove the key from the top of the shaft.</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove the spacer and thrust washer.</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove the reverse gear.</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove the clutch collar.</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove the thrust washer, spacer and low or first gear.</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove the first or second gear.</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove the spacer and thrust washer.</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove the clutch collar.</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove the thrust washer, spacer and second or third gear.</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove the overdrive or third gear.</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove the spacer and thrust washer.</para>
        </step1>
        <specpara>
            <note>
                <para>Remove the roll pin, only if the pin is worn or damaged. The roll pin is difficult to remove.
                </para>
            </note>
        </specpara>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">If worn or damaged, remove and replace the roll pin.</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">If worn or damaged, remove and replace the snap rings from inside the gears (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f13033f9">Figure 159</hotlnk>).
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Inspect all parts. Refer to
                <hotlnk document="s13033_12.xml" xrefid="x1303303">CLEAN AND INSPECT</hotlnk>section.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <figure id="f13033f9" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figg13/G13033f9.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"/>
            <caption>Figure 159. Snap Ring</caption>
        </figure>
    </svcproc>
